New York Yankees pitcher  Andy
Pettitte  broke his left ankle today in the fifth inning against
the Cleveland Indians, the team said on its Twitter feed.  Pettitte, 40, was struck by a ball hit by Casey Kotchman.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
